{
  "text": "Theorem 4 (Gibbard-Satterthwaite's theorem [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). Given a social choice function f over SCOs, assume that there are at least two agents and three outcomes. If f is onto and strategy-proof, then f is dictatorial.",
